title: Oil Prices Edge Lower On Profit Taking
description: Oil prices traded lower on Friday after the U.S. eased some sanctions on the oil industry in Venezuela.  A stronger dollar also prompted traders to book some profits after prices hit their highest levels since September the previous day amid tensions in the Middle East and production outages in Kazakhstan.
